-- South African Coal Export Prices Decline Most in 18 Months
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-07-17T08:54:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-17/south-african-coal-export-prices-decline-most-in-18-months.html
Coal export prices at  South Africa ’s
 Richards Bay , the continent’s biggest terminal for shipping the
fuel, fell the most in almost 18 months.  Coal for  immediate delivery  lost $4.99, or 5.5 percent, to
$85.50 a metric ton in the week ended July 13, according to IHS
McCloskey data on Bloomberg. That’s the biggest decline since
Jan. 21, 2011. The price is quoted on a free-on-board basis,
which excludes delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw at 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lars Paulsson in London at 
